cocktail /ˈkɒkˌteɪl/

(cocktails) 

1. N-COUNT A cocktail is an alcoholic drink which contains several ingredients. 鸡尾酒 

例： On arrival, guests are offered wine or a champagne cocktail. 到达时，客人们可以享用葡萄酒或一份香槟鸡尾酒。 

2. N-COUNT A cocktail is a mixture of a number of different things, especially ones that do not go together well. (尤指不太容易融合的几种物品的) 混合物 

例： The court was told she had taken a cocktail of drugs and alcohol. 法庭被告知她服用了药酒混合剂。 

3. N-COUNT a horse with a docked tail 尾巴被剪断的马

